hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Raizaâ€™s service was amazing. She was very attentive and gave excellent customer service. The food was delicious and she helped me pay the bill at the end. I really appreciate it
Merci boku po!
Masarap po!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
This hotel is amazing and unique. We normally stay in a 5 star hotel in Paris once a year and this will now always be our first choice.
I'm almost reluctant to tell you how good this hotel is in case they are fully booked !
It is a historic building (google it !) that has been wonderfully restored.
Now it has fantastic rooms, brilliant staff and that's before I mention the swimming pools and club facilities.
I arrived grumpy and left feeling so relaxed.
A special thanks to the housekeeping staff who kept our room super clean.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Wonderful location, delicious food and excellent service (Raiza you are great, thank you).
Hotel is very nice. excellent renovation and style. Enjoyed the stay and hotel staff was very helpful.
If you are in Paris it is definitely worth the visit.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We had a fantastic lunch at the hotel Molitor, Great food, and Amazing service, with special Mention To Mr. Marco, that was one of the best chef de rang ever. Always super gentle and attentive to our every Need. Thanks To him for sure We Will Come back to eat there.
Super recommended.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Beautiful hotel. Beautiful breakfast. Beautiful pool. Omg the one of the stellar pools of the world. Re Movie Life of Pi.
This hotel is so well thought out and presented with style. Nice neighborhood, short walk to metro and adjacent to Roland Garros and PSG soccer venue. Good restaurants close by.

Iâ€™ll stay there every trip to Paris.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: A very well located rooftop to enjoy between Roland Garros and the trendy pool. We had the octopus and a burger, both were well seasoned and tasty. The staff was accommodating, thank you to Angela to provided a great service throughout our lunch.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Hotel was clean, warm & friendly environment feeling. Staff were nice & very accommodating . Specially Raiza,Angela and Evita.Most of all we love Kautar who made us feel at home &welcome starting from the time we arrive. They even surprise my friend for her birthday by decorating their room. I would definitely recommend Molitor and would love to stay there again.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Our recent stay at The Molitor coincided with King Charlesâ€™ coronation but it was us that were treated like royalty! What a pleasure to made to feel so special from arrival to departure. Director Gregory and his team excelled themselves with their genuine enthusiasm for our enjoyment and comfort. I was celebrating a special birthday and it seemed that every member of staff was aware of this and I was the lucky recipient of some lovely souvenirs. It was the opening weekend of the wonderful rooftop restaurant and bar and service was slick and seamless watched over carefully by Gregory with all the staff â€œwalking with purposeâ€ which is always a good sign. All in all a delightful stay and we shall spread the word. Thank you everyone.a

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We stayed here for 10 nights in April 2023. The staff were excellent - prior to our stay they arranged airport transfers for us; during our stay they were really helpful. The hotel organised an Easter activity and egg hunt for the children over the Easter weekend, which was a nice touch.

The breakfast menu is excellent - great variety. The staff in the restaurant are really friendly.

Having both an indoor and outdoor pool is great for the children. My children (aged 4 and 6) loved the pools. The indoor pool is quite deep (1.5m), so small children will need to be confident swimmers or be held in the pool. The pools are certainly a highlight of the hotel.

If there was one criticism, the kids menu on the room service and the cafe near the pool was a bit bland and limited options. If the menu was a bit more expansive we probably would have eaten more often at the hotel. But this is a very minor criticism.

Overall, this is an outstanding hotel. I would recommend it to family & friends and we would stay here again.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Iconic hotel in a great setting. BY FAR the best pool in Paris!
The building was first built as a public pool in the 20s. However, it fell into disrepair in the 70s and 80s. It was beautiful restored at the cost of â‚¬80 million in 2014, and every euro invested shows in the quality of the facilities, the rooms, and everything else.

Not cheap, but weâ€™ll worth it if you are a swimmer or an athlete.

NB - hÃ´tel is on the western edge of Paris, about a 20 minute metro ride from the center. The metro connections are good, but you need to be aware that you are on the edge of the city.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Loved everything about this hotel. The staff is truly amazing â€¦ especially the front desk staff. They were so welcoming and so patient with us. Everyone spoke English and made a point to ask if there was anything we needed or needed help with. Truly cannot say enough nice things about the staff. I would go back just for that fact alone!
However, everything else was amazing as well. The rooms were on the small side but still very comfortable. The bed and pillows were the best ever. I slept great all three nights we were there.
The breakfast was included with our package and it was top notch I liked the fact that they served it early too. This allowed us to run in real quick and grab some croissants as we were leaving to go to the airport to fly home.
Pool looked inviting but we were too busy sightseeing to take advantage of it.
We were able to ride the metro and Uber everywhere we wanted to go. Great trip and great hotel!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: We had a wonderful stay at the hotel. Breakfast was good and the staff were excellent- very friendly and helpful. We travelled with 3 kids - 13, 9 and 4 and they were very attentive. Angela was our server at breakfast and at lunch. We used the indoor pool and the kids enjoyed it. We will definitely be back here when we visit Paris!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Angela was super kind even in the early morning.
Everything was perfect food, service, coffee, bread.
Thanks for everyrhing.
I have to come back.
Especually after work out or swim, you can perfectly enjoy this place.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
This is a Modern Hotel with all the grace and elegance you would expect to find in a five-star European hotel. Everything about this hotel is top notch, from the Hand writing Birthday card in our bed. We stayed 5 nights here and the staff was quick to learn our habits and preferences and always hit the mark. In the main restauran Marie Flore alway with a beautiful smile. Edward new our drink preference and super nice. Believe me - you will remember this experience!

I will DEFINITELY stay here again.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We booked this hotel as we are watching a PSG game , we were lucky with the weather so we made full use of both pools in and out a great place to stay we all loved it.
The hotel itself is Ina fantastic area a lovely neighbourhood so itâ€™s pleasant all round

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Awesome atmosphere at the restaurant. The food and service was great ! The design pleasant, but above all the music was incredible and really made the whole thing better (by a live singer). Everything great overall so I recommend this place wether itâ€™s for family or work

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Great dinner. Service and food are both getting better and better over the years. Prices are in line with the quality of the food. Not particularly good value for money but this is worth the visit. To note that you there was also a singer which was particularly pleasant. We recommend this restaurant.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I along with my family (5) we have been members of the ClubSpa Molitor for some years now. We have frequented the restaurant, the rooftop and the club brasserie on countless occasions over the years. Today, after a yoga and swimming session with my husband we met up with 2 of my children for an unscheduled brunch.
It was absolutely delicious the range of foods available were vast the menu with hot meals was just....... as my son of 12 described to the daughter who was unable to attend "it was just too yummy"

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Highly recommend this hotel, especially if you are a swimmer.

Pros:
-Two gorgeous renovated and lovingly refurbished pools-one indoor and one outdoor.
-Very friendly staff.
-affordably priced (what you save on the room more than makes up for taking Ubers to get to the city center).
-great design
-rooms are small but well designed
-nice spa downstairs with many choices for treatments of all kinds. They are especially known for massages (book in advance!)
-nice gift shop

Cons:
-regular rooms are small. It was a little small for two of us for 5 nights.
-restaurant is a disaster. Breakfast food is great, and included. However, the staff have no idea what they are doing. So many things I could mention so I will recount just one. My husband went to dinner one night alone. After being seated no one spoke to him, looked at him - nothing - for 25 minutes! He doesnâ€™t speak French and is polite so he initially lost track of time reading his iPad but then gave up and went back to the room. Dinner food is ok.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We stayed on the 3rd floor which I thought would be quiet but it was terribly noisy. The restaurant was above us but down the way a bit but from early morning around 5:30 am the loud racket began and in the evening until at least midnight was terribly loud. We wore earplugs, white noise on our phones and nothing helped!!!
Nice room, very clean and wonderful breakfast but when you canâ€™t sleep it changes everything!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Hotel Molikor put a huge damper on our first trip to Paris. The staff was unfriendly and unhelpful, there were strict rules at the pool..I was unable to sit near the pool to watch my daughter..unless I was in a swim suitâ€¦and there was a loud dance party that went on until 1 am. Also, the hotel is not in a good neighborhood for walking and exploring. The bathroom was not functional at all. I could go on and on. Do not stay at this hotel with the grumpy staff and miserable accommodations.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: This hotel is very cool with great rooftop and breakfast restaurants. Interesting modern art. It has my favorite pool complex -- both a giant outside pool and an indoor pool as well. Rooms overlook outdoor pool which ised to be a public pool. Has a spa that I did not get to use.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Very friendly staff- accommodating and helpful.
A really nice menu with reasonable prices in a beautiful outdoor rooftop environment.
Recommend to reserve before but the staff tries their best to help.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Bed bugs, vomiting, multiple Dr. visits and ultimately Hotel Molitor refusing to refund our pre-paid money, even though we left immediately and stayed at a different hotel made this the worst travel experience. They insisted, over my strong requests for immediate refund, that we stay the first night. The cigarette smoke from the lobby/pool party literally made me vomit. The music and noise didnâ€™t stop until well into the early morning. We were in a non-smoking room but just outside the window were a balcony of smokers. The room was filthy & that evening while my child didnâ€™t get sleep, she did get bites from bedbugs. The staff refused to take responsibility and just ignored our string of email requests. In the morning I packed and left. I suggest you not even try this hotel unless youâ€™re a partner, a smoker, or donâ€™t value basic health & safety.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Had a nice stay generally.
The pool is still great and the rooms are comfortable.
I feel that the restaurant is still not great, only had lunch at the pool club.
The 4 pm check in is really bad, please make it 2:30 or 3 pm, it would be so much better.
The service is so and so, a lot of unexperienced young teams that donâ€™t make you feel it is a 5 star hotel.
The check in was not good.
Also the first day there was a company party at the hotel on a Wednesday, it felt like a New Yearâ€™s Eve party. It was noisy and the general ambiance in the hotel felt really messy.
Next time I will have to check to avoid these kind of parties while weâ€™re staying there.
The elevator to the pool, is still a problem.
People outside de hotel guest and service are using this elevator, so it takes forever to get down to the pool. Also itâ€™s weird to be with people in the elevator that are going for dinner when your are in your spa rope.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: We stayed for three nights and had a large room with a balcony and pool view. It was really hot in Paris so the pool was great. All the hotel team were so helpful. I can not fault the service. Breakfast ends at 10 but even when we were late they accommodated us. The rest of the team were always friendly and helpful. There was a party when we arrived and they apologised for the noise (which wasnâ€™t a problem) and said we could join if we wanted to.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Molitor si an outstanding Property in the 16th district of Paris. Nice hÃ´tel, Nice Room, perfect roof top for drinks or dÃ®ner. The pool is fantastic. The hÃ´tel, Howeyer, allows ils guest to stay at the pool until noon. Not only is the rule a bit stupid but you havÃ© late Check you just donâ€™t havÃ© a chance to enjoy the ppol. The pool staff has been very unpleasant and rude asking us to leave the pool in the aftternoon even alter a multiple Day stay. Poor management. Never seen this before. Dommage.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: We visited the Molitor as a family and had a wonderful welcome, especially by Lise! Nothing was too much trouble for her in the run up to our visit and she was always available and ready to help with any questions or advice. We felt very well looked after and had a fabulous stay. Thank you Hotel Molitor and thank you Lise!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: What seemed to be a lovely hotel, soon became a very disappointing stay. First we were put in a room that stank of cigarette smoke only to be told that we couldnâ€™t be moved till the next day, then the next day we were out sight seeing and received a message explaining that we now wonâ€™t be moved as we were not available (As if we were expected to hang around the hotel till they were ready to relocate our room). The room we were in was beneath the rooftop bar and was very noisy till after midnight every night. The first two days of our stay, there was no wifi at all. The hotel said they were having technical issues and that there was only wifi for the staff. The breakfast was tasty but also lacked a 5 star effect as there were not enough plates, bowls or food and we were forced to share our bowls with each other. The final cherry on top was when we couldnâ€™t leave for the airport on time because the concierge had not booked a taxi for us, despite being told on arrival that one had been booked and after we confirmed this the night before departure. We were late for our flight and weâ€™re under a lot of pressure as we had to run to the terminal. Not what one would expect from a 5 star hotel!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Amazing place and food !
Having diner on the rooftop with a view on the pool and the Eiffel Tower is magicâ€¦
Couldnâ€™t be better and this is officially our new headquarter in Paris
Thanks to the whole team for the warm welcome and the kind attention

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Nice rooftop restaurant with good views, good breakfast, and friendly service, particularly from Ketsia at the pool bar. Normally ample outside parking overnight. Since the hotel also allows for health club membership the outdoor pool can get busy during c summer afternoons, best swimming for hotel guests is early mornings.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Stayed here with a friend while spending two days at Roland Garros. Great location for the tennis (not really for anything else though as travel to/from city a bit of a pain).
Although initial impression was great, there was a quick come down during checkin. After asking for a twin set up, I was assured it would only take ten minutes to get the room ready and that we should just wait in the lobby (which strangely lacks any air conditioning).

Well ten turned into 30mins when all we wanted to do is drop off stuff in the room and head straight back out (after telling this staff several times). No apology, nothing to make up for the delay... just a set of inexperienced (and very young) staff put in charge.

Simply unacceptable given the pricing and (apparent) 5* label on the front door.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: The pools are fabulous and deserve 5 stars. But we were kept awake at the weekend by the DJ above us at the rooftop restaurant/bar. Iâ€™m not sure a rooftop DJ playing late into the night is compatible with the hotel function of the building, the basic purpose of which is to provide a place to sleep. We did complain at the time each night (the first night it was after midnight) and the reception staff were very understanding and agreed to ask the rooftop to turn the music down. So full marks to the reception staff. But nil points to the management. The only other niggle was extremely slow hot drinks service at breakfast and no coffee or tea offered at all one morning. So a caffeine-free breakfast, great if youâ€™re on a detox maybe. Again, this was not the fault of the staff, who were working very hard. I would suggest the hotel management could provide self-serve coffee and tea machines, as many 5 star hotels do in a high quality way these days. The location was perfect for us, in a leafy residential area with many great local restaurants within walking distance. To sum up, 1 star for the night noise and lack of coffee at breakfast, 5 stars for the amazing, beautiful pools, this averages out at 3 stars.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
My wife, almost 8-year-old son, and I had a fantastic visit to the Hotel Molitor 15 to 20 April (Friday to Wednesday). Of course, this was mostly because of the heavenly Olympic-sized heated pools (one indoor and one outdoor, featured in the movie â€œLife of Piâ€) that were literally the center of everything. But it was also because the hotel was the perfect home base for our touristy Parisian adventures. In keeping with my TripAdvisor review style, I offer the following additional feedback:

Location. The location is perfect, less than a 10-minute walk from the Metro and next door to Roland-Garros and Parc des Princes, which worked out well for us to catch PSGâ€™s Easter night match-up against Marseille. Charles de Gaulle Airport is about an hour away by regional train/Metro. Longchamp Racecourse is only 3 kilometers away. All the city tourist sites were never more than 30 minutes away by Metro. Disney was an hour by Metro/regional train. Perhaps the coolest thing is that the hotel is across the street from the Paris-equivalent of Super Walmart â€“ Carrefour.

Staff. Everyone was super nice and made us feel welcome. It was clear the hotel has a great thing going, and every staff member is happy to be employed there. We arrived early Friday, and the awesome concierge team tended to our bags while we went to the Eiffel Tower before checking in that afternoon. We especially appreciated the bottled water the concierge gave us before each dayâ€™s escapades.

Rooms. Our large room with king bed and roll-away twin for our son was nice and always clean. Our view of the pool was straight out of the movie. The balcony doors opened halfway if we wanted fresh air, but the balcony itself was not accessible. Still, again, great view of la piscine!

Pool. We swam every day in the outdoor pool â€“ in the middle of April, remember â€“ and it was as invigorating as the movie suggests. It was a little crowded, but not intolerable as itâ€™s so big. The indoor pool was nice, too, and a little warmer.

Restaurant/Bars. Breakfast was fine but overpriced so we only ate it once. Same with dinner, so we ventured out all but one night. Still, here again, the friendly staff was very kind and twice heated up our cold prepared meals we purchased at the Carrefour. The rooftop was closed for renovations, but the staff gave us a glimpse â€“ itâ€™s going to be grand!

Excursions. Eiffel Tower Friday. Arc de Triomphe and the Catacombs on Saturday. Family Day at Longchamp and the PSG game on Easter night. PSG Stadium Tour and River Tour on Monday. Disneyland Paris (crowded!) on Tuesday. Everything was easy to get to and went off without a hitch.

Tips. (1) Book excursions in advance. Youâ€™ll be waiting for hours if you donâ€™t. (2) Take good walking shoes. There are not too many fat people in Paris for a reason. We walked more than 7 miles a day. (3) Remember to buy your Navigo passes (includes Metro and regional trains) at the airport for every day except your last day in Paris. Taking the train to the hotel is fine, but who wants to take it back to the airport in the middle of rush hour with luggage? Our Uber to CDG was 58 Euro with tip. Too easy. (4) Remember Parc des Princes may be a 3-minute walk from the hotel, but you enter the stadium according to your section. It took us 15 minutes to walk with the crowd to our designated entry and exit point. (5) Going to a PSG game? Get your tickets early as the prices will go up. The ones we bought were double the price by game day. (6) Prepare to spend extra money at Disneyland Paris on Premier Access/Standby Pass â€“ otherwise, youâ€™ll wait at least an hour per ride. (7) Visit the Carrefour often for your food and drink needs â€“ youâ€™ll save a ton a cash. (8) If there is still a COVID test requirement to re-enter the United States, remember to get tested the night before you leave at one of the many pharmacies in the city. The process is very easy, including adding the documentation they provide to the United app.

Bottom Line. Just book it. We used United Vacations, so the holiday was a package deal. For the money (and the pool), itâ€™s easily the best hotel in Paris. Especially if you have kids, I guarantee youâ€™ll thank me later.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We were in Molitor for a weekend stay and we were absolutely amazed by the stunning design of the hotel, the very spacious and comfortable room, great breakfast, but mostly the lovely service we received from the staff. Always very nice, positive and going the extra mile to help you and make your stay as comfortable as possible!
Thanks to the Team and big congratulations to the Management!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Well, you know the large prices for the tiny rooms in Parisian hotels. Molitor is a good choice, especially if you travel by car. With public transport it is a bit tricky and you will add taxi bills. The room rate is in the high range, but you pay for the pleasure to stay at an icon of the 20th century Paris and be able to use the heated outside pool. All in all, I felt more in a 4-star Novotel-type hotel than in a 5-starrer, given the spartian room and bathroom design.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Chef Salah and Valerie treat me wonderfully for this late dinner. The supreme de volaille was Valerieâ€™s recommendation and was executed to perfection by chef Salah. A very nice and kind evening away from home

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Service at the club and the spa has greatly improved since a few months. Special thanks to Ariestini and Cyril ðŸ‘
Checked the roof top bar before the summer but was desappointed by the service that is not in line with the price of drinks. The place is great...you could do much better

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Fabulous Bar in Hotel Molitor thank you very much at Elie, Steven and Cris the staff is friendly and very nice I enjoyed this moment the hotel is beautiful place keep going merci beaucoup see you next time

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection

Hotel furniture dilapidated the carpet was dirty smell badly they blocked 3450 Eur about 1200 Euros above my invoice and not return back until today the internet was very slow and bad however the staff respectable and professional so kind also and helpful we lost the AirPod in the hotel but unfortunately they could not find it

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Wonderful spa in this beautiful hotel. And I would highly recommend Adil for a massage... very intuitive and effective treatment from a charming and professional masseur. If you can stay longer, the art deco pools are incredible.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I was a guest in this hotel for few days. We were suggested to stay there because was near by to the place of friends wedding. The Hotel is absolutely stunning. Top hotel for room, services and products for shower and bath. In our room there it was a stunning view, illy coffe machine and Bose system surrounding. The major WONDERFUL surprise were the clarins brand products available in our bathroom.
A full five stars.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Great location and great service!! Special thanks to Ryan and Laura for the top quality service and the smile on the roof top ðŸš€
Hope the sun and the end of the pandemic will bring more people in the coming weeks ðŸ˜‰

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Perfect weekend stay. The only thing that could have made it better would have been an extra day. My partner loves swimming and I love being lazy, so he did laps in the (Olypmpic size!) outdoor pool and then we both relaxed in the hammam; btw steam rooms are separate for men and women. Breakfast buffet recommended, as is dining outdoors; rooftop view is one for the bucket list. Bright rooms with comfy bed, best nightâ€™s sleep ever. The Clarins products in the bath are a nice extra; divine scent! The renovation is well done. Contemporary but not sterile, revives the senses. Liked staying in this historic hotel.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Okay, a little bit of backstory.

One thing Paris is short of and that is decent-sized open-air swimming pools.

The five-star Hotel Molitor is built around one of the few such pools which used to be public but is sadly, no more.

Therefore the management know they are on a winner by offering such a facility and as a result, charge like a wounded bull for the privilege of staying there.

On a very hot weekend in Paris, we decided to decamp there for the night to escape our apartment which had been converted into a sauna, thanks to the heatwave.
Our hotel rate did not include breakfast so this is what we found.

The service, albeit friendly, was not the most efficient (granted the hotel was full of stressed Parisians seeking relief from the intense heat). The staff appeared to be very young, inexperienced and utterly overwhelmed.

The rooms are small and in that typical â€œwe-are-so-hipâ€ design approach full of flaws when it comes to practical needs. Such as the bedside tables especially on one side, are so small you can barely fit more than your mobile phone. We also had issues with the toilet barely flushing.

The hotel layout means there is just one lift servicing the pool and spa area which meant people finding themselves crowded into the lift. Far from brilliant in a Covid-19 era. Mask-wearing was not enforced inside this area.

The wifi connection was very poor (especially again given the price we were paying). The area around the pool is so narrow that it is impossible to walk past people in their chairs without disturbing them and there were barely enough chairs to begin with.

The rooftop area is fantastic with lovely views of the city, Roland Garros in the distance.

However, the restaurant there was fully-booked (please oh please, management, do suggest to people when they book a room that if they would like dinner too, they need to book in advance.)

We did manage to score a table in the rooftop bar and ordered what was supposed to be â€œtapasâ€ which turned out to be just bread rolls with glass jars of hummus, pepper dip etc. Massively over-priced for what was delivered to our table. Plus the service was pretty appalling; on three occasions we had to stand and wave our arms to attract the attention of waiters.

So in short, with global tourism coming to an almost halt, the hotel will have to rely on locals to survive (best of luck there as the French, especially Parisians, are a highly-discriminating bunch).

But to any international visitors who somehow do find themselves in Paris during a pandemic, I would strongly recommend to stay somewhere else.

You will get far better value for money at smaller Paris hotel with no pool and hopefully better service .. and thus experience the best this city has to offer.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Fantastic Weekend at the Molitor from check in to check out. I was there for my 20 y/o son's birthday and we have been treated like kings. We received an upgrade for the room and the staff even thought about a nice birthday card for Louis. Fantastic souvenir for all. Thanks to the staff.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
So I got in vacantion in Paris at this hotel molitor, the hotel is cute looks good the stuff is a little not on time they maybe sleep sometimes BUT i meet here TARIQ the reception guy he is amazing he managed everything very fast , the room , the service everything even when i had complains he came into and helped us ! hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I have stayed at Molitor many times now and doubt I will ever stay anywhere else in Paris while they maintain their standards. Great pools (heated all year round), very good gym, wonderful staff, unique design, genuinely exciting place to stay. It would be good if they could install a Versa Climbing machine in the gym.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: How do you qualify an experience that is repeatedly exceptional !? Fantastic location, a real haven. Great staff great facilities great food nice room. If only the spa could allow more treatments, it would be just perfect

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I enjoyed my stay very much at the Molitor. I stayed here for 3 nights. I did choose the Molitor for the pools, and I was not disappointed!
Waking up in the morning, going down to the beautiful outside pool, swimming amongst beauty and art. Is wonderful.
The room ( classic) are small, but well equipped. The beds are very comfortable, IPods, good lights and temperature. Beautiful view of the pool. Very nice and helpful staff, both reception, spa and cleaning.
The fitness room is one of the best I have tried. Very clean.
I had a wonderful stay and I will surely come back.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Super nice stay with family of 4. The pools were just the perfect reward after a day of site seeing, the kids loved it. The family room was beautifully designed and was very comfortable, overlooking the pool. Also the gym is very well equipped and we liked the club area to hang out.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: This morning I woke up after a very good nightâ€™s sleep in a quiet hotel and a luxury bed. Then an early morning swim, a French breakfast with croissants and a massage. A great entourage of a hotel built around an iconic classical outdoor pool. Highly recommended to try this out if you have some spare leisure time in Paris.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
have you ever looked forward to staying somewhere nice and then feeling let down when it doesn't live up to the photos online? Well this place is the opposite - it was even better than all the pictures you can see. From the moment you walk into the lobby with a funky painted Rolls Royce the place just makes you smile.

the check-in staff were fantastic - we arrived early but our room was ready and they made us very welcome. The room was really nicely appointed, the restaurant (we just had lunch) was great (albeit not cheap - but great food and service).

The outdoor pool is amazing - what a great facility. It was November, so outdoor bathing was a little less appetising than maybe in summer, but we still had a swim. The atmosphere was fab - such as historic feel. The indoor pool also has the same amazing atmosphere. Both pools were a great size.

the local area is also nice - right opposite Roland Garros for tennis fans and easy walk to the Metro system and buses. Local bars etc all good.

literally not a bad word to say about our trip - thanks so much!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Positives: the outdoor pool is clearly amazing and was lovely to use after a hard day's sightseeing. Breakfast very good. Concierge extremely helpful.

Negatives: on arrival, the 2 connecting rooms we had pre-booked & confirmed online for our family of 4 were â€œno longer availableâ€. This caused a prolonged, tedious hassle at check-in, as they didnâ€™t know where to put us. The hotel's attitude was more "aloof shrug" than apologetic & they did nothing to compensate.

We were eventually allocated 2 rooms on the same floor but a long way apart (luckily our children were old enough for this to be OK). Beware if you have young children & connecting rooms are essential!

There was an overpowering, sickly fragrance in the air-con system piped throughout the hotel - entrance and bedrooms. What on earth is the point of this? But with the bedroom window open to get rid of fragrance there was noise from the bar downstairs until the early hours.

Standard rooms are modern but small. Tiny bathroom with glass walls. Some lights in the room did not work, including the bedside light - only after several hours passed & repeated requests to Reception was a lamp found by a lovely maintenance guy.

Overall an OK if extortionate stay but only because of the pool.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Lovely staff, friendly and helpful.
Pleasant stay with the family.
Good standard all round despite the weather being bad.
Breakfast had a few options, unfortunately no halal options. Swimming pool was great

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Another lovely stay at The Molitor. Relaxing bed and pillows. The room overlooks open air pool. Shower luxurious with clarins products.
Breakfast is varied and plentiful. Pain au chocolat is the best!Great location and near to subway and lots of restaurants.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Staff was incredibly friendly and helpful but never fussy or formal. Beautiful parks and gardens nearby. Excellent spa and the most stunning hotel swimming pool I've ever seen, always heated, Very cool art collection and a graffiti-covered Rolls Royce convertible in the lobby. Highly recommended

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: The Hotel is pretty nice, but it's not a real 5 stars hotel. I think the main thing here is the pool which is very big and beatiful, except that the rooms are quite nice, but nothing special. Breakfast is pretty good, some choices, I loved the bacon.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: If you want to experience the french arrogance, that's a perfect place ! It's a shame because the hotel is well located and confortable and the history and the renovation is well done. It could be good with a good management.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: We stayed with our teenagers : this hotel has the best pools! We could swim in the indoor pool in the morning, and we could enjoy the outdoor pool in the late afternoon after visiting beautiful Paris. Hotel has amazing modern and street art pieces throughout. Food and rooms were great (amazing pastries at breakfast). The only negative comment is that on the first day that we arrived, we were sent to the next door of the hotel to access the roof top restaurant (which we could not access through the hotel because the rooms were not ready). There is a private club and the staff acted very condescending towards us, telling us Â« this is a private club Â» instead of directing us to the roof top. If there is a family of 4 that looks tired and enter the Â« private club Â» early afternoon, chances are their room is simply not ready and they should be directed to the roof top restaurant ! ;-) Thatâ€™s the only negative comment I have. I will be going back to this great hotel.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Stayed 4 nights and found the hotel to be clean, modern, great staff, excellent free breakfast with many choices. Cool works of art throughout. Visit would have been perfect if hotel was located closer to central Paris but thatâ€™s out of their control. Itâ€™s about 1/2 mile from Metro subway which was easy to get around inexpensively. I did not use the pool but it looked great and seemed to be a hit with other visitors.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I stayed for the weekend at Molitor. I was disappointed by the general service and particularly the unwelcoming behavior of the staff, especially at the front desk area.

Before arriving, we asked if it would possible to check in at 2 pm on the day of arrival. We received this answer from the hotel â€œIf you want to have an early check-in, please make sure to book the previous night. I kindly ask you to note that check-in is from 4:00 pm and check-out at noon. Indeed, at 2:00 pm, no rooms will be available as our guests won't have left yet the hotel.â€

On the day of departure, we called the reception to ask if we could checkout a little bit later. We were told â€œthe check-out policy of the hotel was noon and no laterâ€. All of this happened while the hotel was nearly empty with just a few clients. In short, hotel staff seem to resent customers or think they are better than everybody else because they work at the Molitor! There are far better hotels in Paris to stay at with more welcoming staff. I do not recommend this hotel. Not worth the price.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
This was the second 5star hotel I stayed in during a six week touring holiday of Europe and all have been judged fairly against each other!

Yes , the pools are outstanding, and the staff are are super friendly, however you donâ€™t sleep in the pool .

My bedroom (suite 120) was also really very nice, although at â‚¬680 a night it should be.... so why not a 5 star rating from me?

1) the food both room service and breakfast is really not up to the quality it should be, in fact the breakfast room cannot cope with the amount of guests in the hotel. Itâ€™s a real bun fight unless you get there early. Food choices limited and not enough staff.

2) my biggest and most concerning gripe was the state of the huge terrace that 120 comes with ( and that you pay for) it was quite simply very very dirty.

The wooden flooring was absolutely filthy and so were all the tables and chairs, it looked like there had been a huge party previously to me taking over the room and the cleaners had not bothered to even attempt a suitable clear up.... a bit disappointing as this is a 5 star hotel!

However would I stay again.... yes most certainly because the hotel rooms and facilities are superb, I just wouldnâ€™t pay for breakfast or pay extra for an outside terrace or bother with room service, I would probably then give it 5 stars myself

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I stayed at the Hotel Molitor during a work event and was happy with it. The hotel is pretty new and it has a very modern design.

It has a very generous swimming pool in the middle and you can see how attractive it can be on hot days.

The bedrooms are ok - a bit too small for my taste, but comfortable nonetheless.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Great hotel, modern rooms and all amenities and services available. Situated in a great part of Paris.
Overall a very lovely experience. The pool is just amazing and can be experience summer and winter in the indoor side.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
The question that everybody in Paris is asking these days is where to stay cool and escape the scorching heat. The answer is highly evocative and summed up in a single name: Molitor.
This MGallery Serenity Collection Hotel is everything you expect and much more. A few blocks from the metro Porte dâ€™Auteuil this wonderful haven is yet miles and years away. The Art Deco atmosphere has been superbly restored and mixed with contemporary street art to create a unique decor. And yes, the two swimming pools Molitor has been famous for since the 1930s are simply incredible! They are huge, beautiful, spotlessly clean, perfectly equipped and deliciously odorless. And swimmers there really mean business as they relentlessly do laps from the very early morning. For the others who just want to relax there are comfy pool mattresses,immersed benches and elegant deckchairs.
The rooms look out over the summer pool and have all amenities you can expect from a five star property, with special mention for the fragrant Clarins toiletries and the most comfortable beds weâ€™ve ever had anywhere in the world. No kidding: theyâ€™re amazing!
The cherry on top is precisely the rooftop restaurant from where you can see the Eiffel Tower in the background but more uniquely the Roland Garros courts, especially the newest Simonne-Mathieu, right over which our table was. For tennis fans like us this was definitely quite something! The food was excellent and fresh enough to be truly enjoyed despite the current heat. Our waiter, Benjamin, was nice and friendly, and his recommendations all perfect.
Breakfast this morning was also very good, with a buffet offering a huge choice of particularly tasty products: excellent bread, croissants, cheese, fresh fruit (with even passion fruit), avocado toasts, a whole selection of fresh fruit juice including a delicious detox one, several gluten free products (with carrot cake the best ever, perfectly flavored with just the right crispy frosting) and even dim sum. Everything we had was excellent and there again the service was courteous and pleasant.
Floriane at the conciergerie welcomed us with a kind note and beforehand StÃ©phanie had made sure our stay would be perfect. And it was!
A great thanks to the whole staff for such a restful and enjoyable time!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Loved this hotel- especially as a swimmer . Fantastic outdoor pool (although busy on weekends) and indoor poor. Also pretty good gym. The rooms were modern and beds were super comfortable . On down side- check in was very slow, limited food service options (e.g.. don't try and get dinner before 7pm -even room service) and the inadequate block out curtains which were not supportive of sleeping in beyond 7am in summer. Staff super friendly, cafes available within 500m walk . Would definitely stay again given the opportunity.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Beautiful pool and nice roof deck bar/restaurant, but on the FAR edge of Paris--at least a 40 minutes taxi/subway ride into central Paris. The hotel is directly across the street from both the PSG stadium, the French Open complex, on the FAR edge of Bois du Bolougne. The rooms are modern, though not particularly spacious with nice amenities (robes, Nespresso machine). The gym is also very nice, but I did not visit the spa.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I loved the Molitor. It was once a public lido with indoor and outdoor pools that fell into disrepair and has now been largely rebuilt and turned into a hotel with taste and awareness of its fascinating history. Both indoor and outdoor pools have been restored and the urban art, from its period in the 1990s as a rave venue has also been conserved in places. It has a great vibe, whether or not you love to swim. Its rooftop bar has cocktails as good as its wonderful view over Paris. Its location is great, especially for Roland Garros or the Parc des Princes, but equally there is a direct metro line into central Paris. Staff are helpful and friendly and rooms beautifully designed with unique art, and perfectly clean and quiet. Whatâ€™s not to love?

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I have stayed here many times in 2019

Lovely hotel Great rooms Excellent facilities and free water and soft drinks. The two pools indoor and outdoor are superb

Staff are engaged and caring

Not on the middle of Paris but worth staying

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Love this hotel. Love the spa. Love to get my hair cut in Paris. Cyril in Spa Molitor gave me a grÃ©Ã¢t new style & I hope I can get another appointment with him when we come next year for the French Open Tennis tournament @ Roland Garros.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I paid an outrageous sum to stay at this so called iconic hotel. At 1130 at night there was still a party raging at the famous pool that was supposed to close at10. If they want to promote this as a frat hotel where you party till2am that is fine but that is not the image they portray nor is it what I expect for this price. I hope they made a lot of money off the crowd because I would never recommend it nor stay here again.proximity to Roland Garros onl6 goes so far.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Located 2 minutes from Roland Garros, this 5 star hotel is the ideal spot to stay during the French Open if you love tennis. The service is excellent, the rooms modern and clean, the pools and spa are top notch, and the breakfasts are scrumptious and included. Besides, you can mingle with tennis stars of the past and present in the dining room and reception area.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: If you love to swim, this is the most fabulous place in Paris. It was my third time. It has both an indoor and outdoor pool. There is also an art gallery with modern art. The breakfast is great. The rooftop restaurant has a distant view of the Eiffel tower. Service was great too. Will come back!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Currently staying at hotel during Roland Garros tournament. Rooms go for 600 to 1.200 Euro per night given proximity to grounds. Which is fine.

However, one cannot sleep. There is a party on the rooftoop (which actually is the fourth floor) and the room windows have zero noise cancellation. Hence, you hear everything in your room including the pulsating music.

I am at loss of words. The hotel makes approx. 80 to 100k room revenue per day (!) during Roland Garros. Why ruin the sleep of all hotel guests for some additional (maybe 5k?) party revenues!?

The core competence of a hotel - especially of a 5* city hotel - is to provide a good night sleep. Not to run Ibiza style parties.

It took multiple calls, a visit to the lobby, the hotel manager coming to my room and another call for them to shut the music down. The party is still going on and you hear everything.

Apparently I am not the first one to complain. But management does not seem to care. Btw: There is NOT one line about these parties on the web site.

Clear advice: Do NOT stay here. You might save some time to get to Roland Garros, but this does not help you when you canÂ´t sleep.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
This is a great hotel whenever you stay there but if you attend the French Open then it's unbeatable!
Nice modern and comfortable rooms, friendly staff, an amazing swimming pool, a good restaurant at reasonable prices.
Very highly recommended!!!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We had a wonderful weekend. We went for my boyfriend's birthday and we had the pleasure to discover Clarins beauty care products on the bed !

Breakfast was delicious with many choice and we also appreciated the rooftop of the hotel. We're planning to come again for this summer.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: This is definitely a wow factor hotel. The Art Deco design is amazing and the outdoor pool area stunning.For fitness there is both a substantial indoor and outdoor pool , great gym and wonderful spa with Hamman and sauna. The bar and brasserie and club room all with nice outside spaces are ideal for drinks and snacks.The rooms are nicely decorated but all quite small although the terrace of the executive rooms is massive ( about 4 times the size of the room) . There was building work going on which was quite noisy and also some of our groups rooms smelt which when staff were told about it they merely replied saying they knew about it!. Iâ€™m sure the smell and noise will be resolved so apart from the size of the rooms this is a great hotel

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Stay over in a family suite for 3 nights. Room/apartment was very spacious and confortable. It is quite amazing how they renovated this historic building and converted it into a modern hotel. Staff are friendly and helpful, many facilities including the two swimming pool and located in a quiet part of paris. I will definitely go back.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: This is our second extended stay here, weâ€™re staying 10 days and they never disappoint. The hotel, restaurant, spa, gym & pool staff are all very friendly, professional, accommodating and genuinely warm people. The Hotel is kept clean, has many exciting paintings, murals, displays, many small areas to sit and every space and corner is well thought of. The indoor and outdoor pool are as magnificent as described in the movie â€œLife of Piâ€. The gym is well equipped & spacious. The breakfast buffet has great choices and the menu has variety of delicious options- I canâ€™t say enough about their staff - every one are so professional, genuinely warm and friendly. They work as a team and they just donâ€™t stop, itâ€™s a very impressive operation. Periodically they present us with special snack & beverage in our room. They surprised us one evening with Champagne and snacks for celebrating our Engagement anniversary and choosing to stay with them. This is home for us when we visit Paris. We highly recommended everyone to experience the special treatment and wonders of Hotel Molitor. Sincerely Dr. John & Jenn (Delaware- USA)

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Amazing stay with my fiancÃ©, during the weekend of 10 February 2019. The hotel is great, amazing, all original... clean, staff is very helpful and very kind. Just charming, with the SPA, the pool, 2 swimming outdoor and indoor pool. Just perfect. And itâ€™s a mythic place with a historyâ€¦ for me is important...

I used that opportunity and that place to ask my fiancÃ© to marry me ! the hotel staff helped me to prepare the surpriseâ€¦

Special thank you to Concierge team Jonathan Benhamou and Tarik.. ..they were amazing helping me to prepare a surprise for my fiancÃ© and myself, moment I used to ask my fiancÃ© to marry me.. was amazing moment. We will remember all our life..

Jonathan spent 1 week to prepare everything. he was amaizing.

Also big thank you to Florent BOURGON for helping us to prepare our stay and facilitate our arrival...

Amazing conciergeâ€™s, great staff, place to be, place to stay, AMAIZING!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: The staff were very friendly and helpful. Our room was lovely, over looked the pool and was clean and bright. The breakfast was great, lots of hot and cold options. Was all fresh and refilled regularly. We always try to order in french but the staff speak excellent English. My only gripe was there wasn't a lot of TV choice, you had to pay extra for channels. Although you are in France it is nice when hotels have some English channels available too. We spent most of our time out of the hotel, it was just when we returned late in the evening so it wasn't a problem. It is a short distance from the main tourist sites so we got an Uber for anything from 10 - 22 euros, depending where in the city you were going. It cost us 55 euros each way from Paris CDG airport via a taxi but we could have got an Uber for about 43 euros but we had already booked ours.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: My friends and I stayed at this hotel and our visit was wonderful. We wanted to go sightseeing and the concierge manager Tarik Zaid helped us so much. He got us tickets to everything we wanted to see for a great price including the soccer game that my brother wanted to see. Tarik went above and beyond with all of our requests. The front desk stuff William was also very helpful and very nice. Iâ€™m looking forward to going back to Paris and staying at this hotel again soon.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Stayed there one night (Dec. 15). Conveniently close to our daughter's appt but that's about all there is to it. Check-in took for ever and ever (priority desk unattended, just one employee who took ages to check in other guests) until we blew up and managed to draw somebody's attention. As Platinum members we were upgraded to a luxury room on the 1st floor (we had asked for an upper floor)--nothing fancy though. MyBed, Nespresso coffee machine with a meagre supply of coffee (4 capsules and it took 35 mn. to get some more on Dec. 16), plenty of towels. To make up for the check-in disaster the lady in charge of the reception sent up a basket of fruit with an apology--hatchet buried. The decoration is the totally commonplace (and to our eyes hideous) combination of livid greens, funereal blacks and dismal greys which pass for "elegant" and "modern" in Paris nowadays. The employees are dressed in polo shirts and tan chinos which are meant to give them a "sporty," "cool" look in keeping with the various stadiums in the vicinity--we prefer the suits and dresses in the Prague or Versailles Mgallery--do they wear shorts in summer, one wonders. The spa prices are extortionate but aren't they always. A special mention for the very agreeable barman (the man with a splendid beard) and the young man who checked us out (perhaps he was extra nice because he thought we might bite).

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Stayed here for the PSG vs Liverpool match - could not be better placed for the ground.

The hotel itself is very chic and Uber cool - however without the attitude that usually goes with Uber cool. Everyone was very friendly.

The pool looked great but I didnâ€™t have time, the bar was fun and I cannot comment on the breakfast as I was too hungover to even consider it.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I stayed one night on 28/11, part business and also to watch the football game at Park du Princes, for which this hotel is ideally located, as for Roland Garros! From arrival the reception and handling of check in, reflected a really big commitment to personal and friendly, helpful and considerate service. I am a Diamond Hilton member and am used to good treatment, but this was exceptionally good for a one off stay. All staff including the house keeping lady were really nice, but three people need mentioning, Prisca on reception, Stephanie on Concierge and Angela in the restaurant. All three were so helpful, warm and provided exceptional service at all times. The only negative would be the room rate was high in my opinion for a twin.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: Excellent top hotel, just around the corner from Parc des princes, highly recommended! Alcohol was a bit expensive but it is Paris so was expected. Breakfast had a superb selection and good section for gluten free eaters. Will stay again!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: The pools are fantastic : opening hours, ambiance, lights, temperature, length, ( a covered space to leave the towel would be appreciated in rainy and cold weather , going around the barrier isnâ€™t ideal) the hammam isnâ€™t really hot, not enough hook to hang the dressing gown, only 4 , if more than 4 persons in the hammam then sharing the hooks.., the quiet space is for residents and members , again, too small. We thoroughly enjoyed the buffet or a la carte breakfast, plentiful and delicious but if one comes down after 10h00 on Sunday morning then one has to queue for a table and eats what is left, not everything is refreshed.It was my birthday , no special treat !!!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
We stayed in this hotel following a Belgium/French battlefield tour for the centenary of the Armistice. What a wonderful hotel. All the staff were delightful and enthusiastic-including at 4.00am when we had to leave for the airport.
Breakfast has a lot of variety and the staff again are very pleasant.
We stayed here for the pools. It is nearly impossible to stay at a hotel in a large city like Paris with such a wonderful pool-not only one pool but two. Absolutely a godsend.
Would definitely stay here again. Congratulations.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Molitor is a great place with a fantastic atmosphere. Best of all is the staff... I love it it is my second home away from home.
great food, great gym and swimming pool. the rooms are nice, the brasserie and the roof terrasse restaurant ( in spring and summer) delightful.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I regularly go to Molitor for business or private breakfasts, lunches and dinners - the food is delicious, service is great, and there are not many places in Paris where you can eat by the pool or in a restaurant that feels simultaneously chic and relaxed. + the rooftop is great when the weather's nice.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
As a huge fan of Paris and architecture, I loved (love?) Molitor.
Itâ€™s one of the best places to stay in Paris and given the history I strongly believe that itâ€™s sticks to its name and reputation.

Personally I loved spending my time on the rooftop!

I strongly recommend this place.

Cheers.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
I have booked 2 nights in this incredible place. Booked a deluxe room, the first contact with the reception was perfect. the place outside and inside immediately capture you. front desk is really what I do like. Casual and chic, we are in a 5 stars a real one. In 2018 and not in 1918. Arrived in the room I discovered that we have been upgraded to a the tremendous suite with a terrace on the outside pool (as all accommodation have a front line view on the outside pool.). this suite (I suppose called pool suite) is a true master suite. I will not comment so much...perfect! you have all. One very positive point. Absolutely sound proof...inside. And the coffee in your bathrobe outside on your terrace is a dream.
The swimming pool (you have 2, one is inside) is lovely and huge for Europe and the "decor" is superb. In this mid October with 80.5Â°F outside...It was incredible.
Then walking around in the hotel is a pleasure : street-art, pictures good reminiscence of the last century.
The brasserie (you need to book as appreciated by neighbors) offers a good fusion food, fair price, very good wine list. And I was really happy as Friday and Saturday you do have the opportunity to experience a D.J. so very good sound track. ..In fact even when there is no D.J. the sound track is perfect.
The concierge desk is ultimate and really Tarik you have eased my life in a professional and kindly way...and I am a "needy" customer. So "chapeau bas".
Breakfast is really a 5 stars one...organic, gluten free, no-fat dishes...the top. Whatever your body need is there. Brigade is efficient and to be noticed, we are in France but they are numerous and helpful. At the end of the day. An exceptional place. Absolutely quiet from outside, very dynamic for eyes and ears, great for the taste..and with cabs very easy to go to all what you need to see in Paris. I never thought I will find in Paris what we do get in Wien, Riga or Budapest.
To be noticed too, as Platinium Accor le club member it was the first time I was granted a card which offer you free soft drink when you need them whatever the place in the hotel...I think other Accor 5 stars should take this as a benchmark.
Conclusion : a dream and now my Paris stop over will be located there.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
Stayed at this hotel to celebrate my girlfriend's birthday and it didn't disappoint. It's a wonderful hotel with a fascinating history and had been on my hotel bucket list for quite some time.

It's quite a way out to the west of Paris, so it's not the best location for all the touristy things on offer, but it's a great location for the sporting stadiums nearby.

Check in was simple, as an Accor gold member we were given two x free drink vouchers, which we used in the bar by the outdoor pool. Unfortunately we weren't upgraded, which seems a common theme in France, compared to other countries which treat status members a bit better. I also mentioned in booking and via email that we were celebrating my girlfriend's birthday, but there was no mention of this / no special touches which you would expect from a 5* hotel. For staff / 5* touches I would give this hotel 2/5, the only reason I gave it 5/5 was the building itself and the uniqueness of the property.

The rooms were nice, we had a room which faced the outdoor swimming pool. The bed was very comfortable, the WiFi worked well and the bathroom was good.

There is an indoor pool as well as the outdoor pool, and both pools are very much "swimming pools". The outdoor pool was really cold on a September afternoon, which was a bit disappointing. The outdoor pool also had a jacuzzi area as well as some water jets for hydrotherapy.

I would definitely return to this property, not for the staff but for the amazing pool and the wonderful history of Molitor.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: We had a great stay here, the upgraded room was amazing, comfy bed and spacious room with a window overlooking the interior pool which is the staple of the hotel. The food was average but would definitely go again

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: After an exhausting bike ride the Molitor is the perfect destination in Paris a trendy unique hotel with friendly efficient staff set around two amazing pools indoor and out. A second visit for us and Iâ€™m sure we will be back. Great roof top restaurant with views over Paris and the Eiffel Tower light show at night.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I stay here often when I come to Paris for business. I love how they have renovated/re-done this historic Parisian location. The rooms are a little on the small side but beautiful and views of the pool are beautiful. Staff are hard working and friendly. The food and menu as well as brasserie are delicious (I would expect nothing less from a Luxury Paris location !) Only downside is the noise from the outdoor / terrace bar and the overhead light fixtures are too bright and easy to hit your head on!

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews: I was a bit hesitant to book this hotel due to the location and the critical reviews from others citing that the room is small and noisy from the rooftop restaurant and the pool but I had a wonderful stay with the families and friends while visiting Paris. First off, I had very little expectation in terms of service and facility due to most hotels in Paris being overcrowded, underwhelming service and overprices in general. However, my perception changed the moment we checked-in all the way to check-out. The only hiccup I can point out was the lack of readily available valet personnel when we arrived by car - I had to park the car by the curb and go get someone to come out and help. Once I got the attention of the staffs, everything went smoothly there on. Every staffs that I interacted with were friendly, kind and showed that they cared. The pool suit that we stayed in had the modern french chic decor with good sized bathroom. We were positively surprised by the welcome amenities (fresh bottled juice and chocolate) once we were situated in the room. But what made the experience even better was when the bell staff brought little teddy bears once he saw the kids in the room (he didn't speak any English but told me something in French but I understood from the body language that he would be back and brought a little surprise for the kids to be happy). I think this type of attention is what creates a great 5 star hospitality. As for the facility, the hotel is on the modern chic with lots of playful paintings on the wall and colorful ambiance. The pool was well kept but it was really crowded from the gym members coming on a weekend to relax. The rooftop bar/restaurant has a great vibe but the menu and the meal quality was just OK (for a french standard). The quality of service by the staffs on the other hand, superb! Everyone made sure that out family was having a good time, helped with the strollers to move in and out of the narrow passages, etc. The quality of the drinks and food from the lobby bar, pool service and in-room dining was just ok for the price but the staffs really made up for the average food/drinks. Overall, we all had such a great time while staying at Molitor and would definitely come back as long as the hospitality quality remains the same - we all left this place with a big smile.

hotel: Hotel Molitor Paris - MGallery Hotel Collection
reviews:
The pools were the highlight of our stay. The hotel is an oasis in Paris on a hot day. On arrival the reception staff were very welcoming. We were turned away from the rooftop bar as they were 'full' - although the place was almost empty and we only wanted an aperitif. The balance between private functions and hotel guests doesn't feel quite right.
We experienced abrupt and unhelpful responses from staff at breakfast and when trying to locate the spa facilities. A few unfriendly staff, but most were pleasant.
We had a couple of room design flaws - we could hear music from the rooftop bar until very late. Also no bedside lights, but a large room light which you keep hitting your head on!
